<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-26T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.6511/154: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-26T18:00:00-04:00">September 26, 1940—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>320. The Department’s 319, September 25, 7 p.m. Jones and Guinle signed,
                            at 3:30 p.m. today, the exchange of letters on the steel project and the
                            texts as cabled to you yesterday were immediately released to the
                            press.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>